\title{exponentiable object}
\date{2023-03-05T12:05:45+01:00}
\taxon{definition}
\author{jonmsterling}

\import{base-macros}


\p{Let #{E} be an object in a category #{\mathcal{C}} such that all binary cartesian products with #{E} exist. We say that #{E} is \em{exponentiable} when the product endofunctor #{-\times E} on #{\mathcal{C}} has a right adjoint, which we shall write #{E\Rightarrow-}.}